1 3. Paying the required fee.
2 B. Any person who fails to apply for a renewal in a manner
3 prescribed by the Department, and whose license has expired, may not
4 engage in activities that require a license until the license has
5 been renewed.
6 C. Not later than sixty (60) ninety (90) days before the
7 expiration of the license, the Department shall send written notice
8 of the impending license expiration to the animal shelter operator
9 or commercial pet breeder at the last-known address according to the
10 records of the Department.
11 D. The Department shall provide an online renewal and payment
12 platform on or before January 1, 2026.
13 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
